' §D2.9 funding flow — wallet → funding_sig → gate (Σ≥Δ) → debit → replay.
' One Cosigned yields TWO keys: deploy_id (wire-sig, on-chain identity) and the
' funding key funding_sig = Sig::Ground(pk) (the signer's wallet Σ⟦Ground(pk)⟧).
'
' Source of truth for cost-accounting-impl/d2-9-funding-flow.md (Figure A).
'
' Color palette (house style; cf. deploy-execution-sequence.puml):
'   Actor / Deployer       : salmon  (#F8C3B8)
'   Ingress (control)      : amber   (#FFECB3)
'   funding_sig / settle   : mint    (#C8E6C9)
'   Gate / Replay (fn)     : teal    (#B2DFDB)
'   Supply pool Σ⟦Ground(pk)⟧ (the wallet) : blue (#BBDEFB)
' Semantic arrows:
'   debit / charge         : red     (#C62828)
'   read / conserve        : green   (#2E7D32)
'   deploy_id (decoupled)  : grey-dashed (#9E9E9E)
'
' Render:  plantuml -tsvg docs/theory/diagrams/d2-9-funding-flow-sequence.puml

@startuml d2-9-funding-flow-sequence
!theme plain

skinparam sequence {
  ArrowColor              #444444
  LifeLineBorderColor     #666666
  ParticipantBorderColor  #333333
  NoteBorderColor         #666666
  NoteBackgroundColor     #FFF8E1
  GroupBorderColor        #333333
  GroupHeaderFontColor    #222222
  DividerBackgroundColor  #ECEFF1
}
skinparam defaultFontName "sans-serif"
skinparam defaultFontSize 12

autonumber

actor       "Deployer"                       as D   #F8C3B8
participant "Ingress\nfrom_proto_cosigned"   as IN  #FFECB3
participant "funding_sig\n(accounting)"      as FS  #C8E6C9
participant "Gate\nadmit_by_funding"         as G   #B2DFDB
database    "Σ⟦Ground(pk)⟧\n(the wallet)"     as W   #BBDEFB
participant "CloseBlock\nsettlement"         as CB  #C8E6C9
participant "Replay\nrecompute"              as RP  #B2DFDB

D -> IN ++ : submit Cosigned { wire_sig, pk }
IN -> IN : verify each cosigner sig vs its pk\n(forgery ⇒ reject at ingress)

note over IN #FFF3E0
deploy_id is derived from the WIRE signature
(envelope_sig = Quote(Blake2b256(DOMAIN ‖ wire_sig)))
— on-chain identity, UNCHANGED. It is NOT the funding key.
end note
IN -[#9E9E9E]->> IN : deploy_id := envelope_sig(wire_sig)  [decoupled]

IN -> FS ++ : funding_sig(cosigned)
FS --> IN -- : Sig::Ground(pk)\n(multi-sig: And-fold of Ground(pkᵢ),\nplaceholders filtered)
IN -> G ++ : candidate { funding_sig, Δ_s }

G -[#2E7D32]-> W ++ : read Σ⟦Ground(pk)⟧
W --> G -- : Σ_s
G -> G : is_funded:  Σ_s ≥ Δ_s  ? (Def 19)\nmargin only on the `unknown` branch (F-B)
alt Σ_s ≥ Δ_s  (funded)
  G --> CB ++ : admit ⇒ settlement debit ΣΔ_s
  CB -[#C62828]-> W : debit  post = pre − ΣΔ_s  (checked_sub)
  deactivate CB
else Σ_s < Δ_s  (strict shard)
  G --> D : REJECT (under-funded; no execution, no debit)
end
deactivate G
deactivate IN

== Replay (independent re-verification) ==
RP -> RP : to_cosigned() ⇒ re-derive the SAME funding_sig\n(no drift)
RP -[#C62828]-> W : recompute Σ⟦Ground(pk)⟧ debit
note over RP, W #E8F5E9
Replay reconstructs the verified cosigner set and re-derives
funding_sig, so the settlement-debit map is BYTE-IDENTICAL
to play. Strict compound deploys key on the effective supply
(effectiveΣ = Σ_compound + min(Σ_l,Σ_r)), not raw presence.
end note

note over D, W #E3F2FD
**Σ⟦signer⟧ == Σ⟦wallet⟧** — the pool the gate proves Σ≥Δ
against and debits IS the genesis-seeded wallet Σ⟦Ground(pk)⟧.
Pre-§D2.9 the wire-sig pool was always absent ⇒ never debited.
end note

legend left
| Color | Meaning |
| <#F8C3B8> salmon | Deployer (actor) |
| <#FFECB3> amber | ingress / control |
| <#C8E6C9> mint | funding_sig / settlement (accounting) |
| <#B2DFDB> teal | gate / replay (function) |
| <#BBDEFB> blue | supply pool Σ⟦Ground(pk)⟧ (the wallet) |
| <#C62828> red | debit / charge |
| <#2E7D32> green | read / conserve |
| <#9E9E9E> grey-dash | deploy_id (wire-sig, decoupled) |
endlegend

@enduml
